data.title: High-Performance Connectivity with Highwings 8K 10K HDMI Cable
data.body:
I recently upgraded my home entertainment setup with the Highwings 8K 10K HDMI Cable, and the results have been nothing short of impressive. This certified Ultra High Speed HDMI® cable delivers on its promise of high-performance connectivity.

High Data Transfer Rate (5/5):
The standout feature of the Highwings HDMI cable is its incredible 48Gbps data transfer rate. This ensures seamless transmission of high-resolution content, making it ideal for 8K and 10K displays. The cable supports the latest HDMI specifications, providing a future-proof solution for evolving multimedia needs.

8K and 10K Resolution (5/5):
Whether you're a cinephile, gamer, or content creator, the Highwings HDMI cable unlocks the full potential of your 8K and 10K devices. The cable's capability to transmit crystal-clear visuals and vibrant colors enhances the viewing and gaming experience, bringing content to life with stunning detail.

Certified Ultra High Speed (5/5):
The certification as an Ultra High Speed HDMI® cable instills confidence in its performance and reliability. It meets the stringent standards set for high-speed data transmission, ensuring that it can handle the demands of the latest audio-visual technologies without compromise.

Durable Braided Design (5/5):
The braided design of the cable not only adds a touch of elegance but also enhances durability. The braiding provides additional protection against wear, bending, and potential damage, making the Highwings HDMI cable a robust and long-lasting investment.

Length and Flexibility (5/5):
The 6.6FT/2M length strikes a perfect balance between flexibility and practicality. It provides ample reach for connecting devices while minimizing excess cable clutter. The flexibility of the cable makes it easy to route and manage behind entertainment centers or within wall-mounted setups.

Wide Compatibility (5/5):
The Highwings HDMI cable is compatible with a wide range of devices, including 8K and 10K TVs, gaming consoles, Blu-ray players, and more. Its versatility ensures that it can seamlessly integrate into various home theater and gaming setups without compatibility concerns.

Gold-Plated Connectors (4.5/5):
The gold-plated connectors contribute to stable signal transmission and resistance to corrosion. While gold-plating is a common and effective choice for connectors, additional reinforcement in critical areas could further enhance the cable's durability over time.

Value for Money (5/5):
Considering the high data transfer rate, certification, durable design, and wide compatibility, the Highwings 8K 10K HDMI Cable offers excellent value for money. It's a worthy investment for anyone seeking top-tier performance in their multimedia setups.

Conclusion:
In conclusion, the Highwings 8K 10K HDMI Cable stands out as a reliable and high-performance solution for demanding audio-visual applications. Its data transfer capabilities, build quality, and compatibility make it a top choice for those who prioritize quality connectivity in their home entertainment systems.

data.title: Catproof cables....so far
data.body:
I was needed durable HDMI cable for my kid's Xbox and TV setup, especially one that could withstand the curiosity of our household cats. That's when I found the Highwings 8K/10K HDMI Cable. With a promise of ultra-high speed and a sturdy braid, it seemed like the perfect fit for our needs.

Tthe Highwings HDMI cable felt different from others. It's thick, with a noticeable heft and a braided exterior that screams durability. The connectors are solidly built, giving off an impression that this cable is made to last. The length, 6.6 feet, offered just enough flexibility to connect devices without leaving too much slack for our feline friends to find.

Our main concern was whether it could stand up to the occasional cat attack behind the TV. While we don't let our cats chew on cables, accidents happen, and it's reassuring to know that this cable is robust enough to give us a chance to intervene before any real damage is done. The braided exterior isn't just for show; it provides an extra layer of protection that seems to deter even the most persistent of pets.

Pros:
* Works well with AppleTV and old TCL LCD TV (only 1080p, so not testing "8k" capacity of this cable at all)

Cons:
* Plugs are loose in the HDMI ports (tried multiple different HDMI ports, and they were loose in all of them)
* Label on plug is on "bottom" (narrow side of the trapezoid) instead of "top", so need to retrain how to orient before plugging in

For my specific purpose, where these are connecting an AppleTV mounted on the back of a TV to said TV, the cons aren't really much of an issue. I do wonder how well it will work with the looseness of the plug though (will it loosen and fall out over time?) I might put a piece of tape to hold it in the port more securely.

data.title: Tested fine up to 4k @ 144Hz. Nice jacket, but a little stiff.
data.body:
Review for Highwings 8K HDMI Cable Long 2.1 30FT/9M:

I purchased this cable to replace an Amazon Basics 25ft that was rated for much lower bandwidth. The other cable worked, but was 'fussy' about signal and a bit thicker. I also needed that extra 5 ft. due to a room change.

This Highwings cable has been used between a Galax 4070ti and a Samsung S90C successfully at 4k 144Hz with no issue. Both the PC and the TV detect everything as it should and I've not had any questionable disconnects, etc. While this does work, if you're using this off of a GPU, you may wish to get an active cable. The 4070ti doesn't seem to like driving this with more than one other display. I normally run 3 monitors plus the TV, but long passive runs like this cause most GPU's to balk at too many displays.

The cable jacket is nice and has a good feel to it. It's also a but thinner than the older, lower specced cable I had before. It is pretty stiff, though. I can't really fault it as that's a lot of signal to push over passive copper.

It's a good buy and lives up to it's specs, maybe beyond, but I've not tested that yet.

data.title: Works fine but something is weird
data.body:
In first place, i give only 4 stars just as a precaution, please, read the last paragraph.

Effectively this is a certified "Ultra High Speed HDMI Cable", i've verified with the "HDMI Cable" app, that's a good start.

In my case i've used to connect my RTX3080 12GB to a Samsung 50" Neo QLED 4K QN90A (QN50QN90AAK),
with previows cables from other weird brands i was suffering of random flickering, sometimes just a couple in 1 hour; with this cable as far as i've tested the flicker is gone, even using the most demanding resolution that my rig can achieve, 3840x2160 @120Hz 10bit YCbCr444; no artifacts, no sound issues, variable refresh rate works fine too, overall it works as expected, i'm satisfied in this regard wtihout doubts.

HOWEVER, i must be clear, there is something weird here that is good that you know, at least in my case, if i use the Samsung built in function to test the hdmi cable the test fails and it recommends to replace the cable, to be honest i don't know if that test is reliable, at least in my real life test this is the 1st cable that works properly without any issues, maybe at 144Hz there can be issues, i have no way to test at that refresh rate so i don't know.
